Fun and new place to eat sushi, but not any cheaper than the average sushi restaurant!  Came for Sunday lunch recently, and there was no wait, which was a pleasant surprise. We were seated and got a rundown of how everything works by a waiter. Obviously you can pick anything off the conveyor belt, where plates range from $1.50 to $6.50, or order off the iPad that each table comes with. If you do the latter, a bullet train will shoot over to your table with your dish.  Overall, the experience is very very fun with all the cool gadgets, the restaurant is very clean and modern, and service is attentive. There’s a variety of rolls, nigiri, and appetizers and large dishes such as ramen and poke bowls for those who don’t want sushi. We paid around $20 per person and wasn’t stuffed, so it is a bit pricey but honestly on par with regular sushi restaurants.  As a tip, the $2.50 (yellow) plates with four pieces of sushi rolls are the best bang for your buck! The ramen and bento boxes also look like good deals.
Excellent ambience with fantastic sushi! Recommended

Highly recommend this restaurant! They have delicious food and cocktails as well as having pretty strict COVID-19 protocols (this is a huge plus for me). They check your temperature as you enter, sanitise your hands, and they enforce social distancing and occupancy limits. All the staff wear masks and you're given a plastic bag to put your mask in while you eat. The bathrooms (and the whole restaurant) are really clean. If you are keen for sushi or some Japanese food, you should definitely give this place a try!

I am absolutely thrilled with this location. The place is fabulous, modern and trendy! Way bigger than the one in Broadway, but with same deal for food. You pay for the dishes you get from the belt, upon the color of the plate, also you can order from the iPad and get it from the kitchen carried by a cute train (or maybe from the robot -so coooooool-). This place is vibrant and cool, also I don't really find it expensive. Plus, alcohol is a great deal here. Asahi for $5? Yes, please!  Place opened at the very beginning of the year, so it is still basically brand new, so expect to wait to be seated. Good thing to know is that you can join the waitlist here at Yelp to reserve your spot if you are on the way. We did it, but still we had to wait, it was Saturday night! The wait i worth it, no worries.  Sushi was really fresh, a quality is good for the price you pay. My favorite rolls were Fiesta Roll, Boston Roll and the classics Hosomakis (Salmon and Tuna). We got some appetizers too like takoyaki, shumai and seaweed salad. Very good as in their previous location.  The only thing I am not really sure is about accommodating big groups in here, I didn't see any big table. Hopefully they will be able to accommodate big parties soon, so we can celebrate there with friends.  Oh, almost forgot it. Get your rewards card. For every $15 spent you get a point, and when you reach like 10 points you get $25 off from your bill. I just did it, using my card from the Broadway location and got the discount, plus a cute tea cup!

caption: Affordable prices, good food and service.

Not a bad place to visit, Can try a little bit of everything for those who can’t make up their mind and nice for the budget. Worked at sushi restaurants before, and the sushi does have a little too much rice for my taste, the fish is a little too thin, but of course this is fitting for the price. Miso and edamame app were good. Ramen dish I definitely had better but for the price it is very comforting dish, the pork pieces however were very hard and dry and had no flavor, I did take the pork pieces home and fed them to my dogs since they were not salty! Definitely a fun place to go with the train belt and robot!

This place is so fun. We came before the pandemic and the rotary aspect was in full swing. You pick the plate you want off the conveyor and pay per plate. If you ordered a kitchen item it would come on a special track on a train. Now, mid-pandemic you order from a tablet and all items are brought out by the train in disposal paper boxes. The staff takes your temperature when you enter and then asks you to use hand sanitizer if you are dining in. Tables are distanced appropriately. The sushi is delicious and fresh as well as kitchen items. The meal is super affordable and fun experience. Give it shot, you will not be disappointed.

I would think that its obvious to place the two separately. presentation of the sushi was amazing, quality of the food is amazing, I will be trying every item on the menu. With recent event they have to limit their seating, I wa sable to order takeout and also dine-in, both times were absolutely great and without issues. Their variety is quite big and looks appetizing when displayed, and does not fail  in flavor either. Overall worth every dollar spent.

Such a cool experience! Great service, robots, and trains.

Cool atmosphere, average quality sushi and slightly high prices. Not super impressed, but worth it for a unique eating experience. There's usually a wait, so plan accordingly and try to join the waitlist.  The rotary is pretty fun and custom orders come on a cute little train on it's own track. The inside is vibrant and new, although it can even be a little too much. Most sushi rotaries are more expensive than conventional so I can't complain too much, but this one feels a bit more so, even charging $2.50 for tea.  Sushi itself is alright, pretty average in my opinion. The sashimi is thick cut and tasty, and scallops, himachi, plus salmon nigiris are all pretty good.  Overall decent experience, something cool to try or go to every now and then!

This place rules. I came here for my birthday with a large group and I called a few days in advance to make sure they would have a spot for me. They were so accommodating and I came in with a big cake that they took to the back for when we were ready for birthday cake time. The sushi was fresh and delicious, there’s an iPad menu at every table you can order specialties from. When you order things from the menu either a robot will bring it to you or the little train on top of the rotary sushi will. So cool!! Super friendly, great service, the atmosphere is fun and the place is brand new and clean. I’m coming back here for the rest of my life for a nice time. They also have very yummy drinks as well and cheesecake from the Cheesecake Factory! This place has it all. 5 stars.
Very delicous stuff there. Sure it's a bit pricey, but it's worth it.
ALWAYS a fantastic experience!!! Love how convenient this location is to home.

(Translated by Google) The only sushi restaurant in southern Chicago. It is not made in Japan but seems to be a Chinese chain. The price range is similar to Korean sushi restaurant. The restaurant design is quite neat and the system to order by train is also fun. As the name suggests a bar, it seems to sell a variety of cocktails and alcoholic beverages. The quality of the rice is a bit too stiff and Nigiri Sushi seems to be made using frozen fish. However, roll rolls and warships are worth eating. There are also bento menus at reasonable prices, so if you want to eat sushi simply, this is the place to go.  (Original) 시카고 남부에 있는 유일한 회전초밥집. 일본에서 만든건 아니고 중국판 체인인듯 하다. 가격대는 한국초밥집과 비슷한 편. 레스토랑 디자인이 상당히 깔끔하고 열차로 주문을 시켜먹는 시스템도 재미있다. 이름에 바가 들어있는 만큼 다양한 칵테일과 주류도 판매하는 것 같다. 밥의 질이 살짝 과하게 고슬고슬한편이며 니기리스시는 냉동생선을 사용해서 만드는 것 같다. 하지만 롤 전반류나 군함 등은 먹을만 하다. 가격이 저렴한 벤또 메뉴들도 있어서 초밥을 간단하게 먹고 싶으면 갈만한 곳이다.
Great place, good food and extremely friendly team. There's a good variety of food on the rotary and the menue and the quality is good.

Overall, it's good and the selection is fun as well as the ways in which food is delivered to you. The two times I went here the deserts were hit and miss (one was almost frozen solid). It's definitely worth going to, but I think there's room for improvement. They also have a robot, so that's pretty cool. I embrace our future robot overlords.

Went last night with my boyfriend to try out rotary sushi bar, and had a great time. The wait was about an hour, we didn't know we could reserve ahead of time, but now we know. The sushi was really good and vast variety, the service was great as well, including the robots and the subway train. The sushi was reasonably priced and you actually know what it is that you're spending when picking your food and piling your dishes which I personally think is really neat. I highly recommend anyone to check this place out it's a cool experience and great sushi!

Great food, reasonable prices (a little bit on the more expensive side, though), and an interesting atmosphere. However, it took us thirty minutes to set a reservation and even longer than that to get a table. The waitress attending our table, however, was very courteous and on top of her game. Kudos to her for her graciousness.

This place is just so freaking COOL! Now I have been to conveyor belt sushi restaurants, but hands down this is the best one so far. First off all, the choices this place has to offer is quite vast. Love sushi? No problem! Hate sushi? No problem! They even have stuff for kids.  Not only was the food really good, the drinks were as well. My favorite cocktail was the spicy mango margarita. However, I also had their sake, and I was not left disappointed.  If you don't like what the conveyor belt options have to offer, or you don't want to wait for a while for an option to come back, they also have an iPad ordering system. It's almost worth trying because of how the food is delivered. Once your order is ready, it's delivered by a train!!  Though they don't take reservations, you can easily put yourself on the Yelp wait-list and plan accordingly.  I can't wait to come back!
